; a Dormouse was sitting
  between them, fast asleep, and the other two were
  using it as a cushion, resting their elbows on it,
  and talking over its head.

  The table was a large one, but the three were all
  sitting on the edge of the table-cloth; "because
  they couldn't get their heads through."

  "Your Majesty should have come earlier," said
  the Hatter. "It's too late now."

  "We must have some wine," the King said to the
  Footman, very severely: "fill this cup for me."

  The Footman filled the cup for him, and handed it
  round as he spoke.

  "I didn't know it was YOUR Majesty," said the
  Hatter. "Indeed, it's only once a year you're here,
  you know."

  "Once a year!" Alice
